OL,3,GHighlands & Eilean Siar
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FDry and frosty with sunny
OL,6,Fspells at first. Cloud will spread
OL,7,Fnorth through the afternoon but it
OL,8,Fwill stay dry as the southerly wind
OL,9,Fstrengthens.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FClouding over through the
OL,12,Fevening. Mostly dry in the north and
OL,13,Feast with the odd spot of rain,
OL,14,Foccasionally heavy outbreaks of rain
OL,15,Fin the west. Strong southeast coastal
OL,16,Fwind.
OL,17,
OL,18,CWednesday:FCloudy at first as bands of
OL,19,Frain push northeast. Showers follow
OL,20,Ffrom the west, some heavy and thundery.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
